{
  "stem": "17299.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Baby carriages were standing outside full with snow, and some which were not full with snow had the blankets and the bottles in it with the milk.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And more people came in.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "It was standing room only, because everyone had to be-- the 1,000 people had to be in probably seven or eight houses.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Even some went in the barns and everything, and in the stables, in order to be off the street.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We-- we thought of the pogrom of 1938.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What must have happened over here may be even worse.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But nobody thought of killing then, even though there was blood and clothing on the floor and the walls.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So everyone was flabbergasted and in shock.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We could not see any other people, and we-- later on, we saw some people-- some I know-- that came from Cologne, and we got informed that a transport from Cologne arrived first.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there were some Jews from Cassel also, and we were the third transport.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and a friend told us, you only can go where they allow you-- otherwise, they shoot you.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And later on we hear a shot ringing out, and so a woman got killed because she had crossed the middle of the street.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And after a while somebody came in and took some people out of the rooms.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "More houses were opened up, because there was no other possibility.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So then we walked to find our friends, and it seems, like I said, in the houses and wherever we went standing room only.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So after a while Nussbaum, who was the transport leader and later the alteste of the Dusseldorf group, came in with somebody else.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "His name was [GERMAN], which was not an angel.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
